&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for Band 5 staff nurses to join our diverse neurosciences ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Neurosciences ward (12E) is a 24 bedded ward (with a 12 bedded Monitored Unit Bay) managing Neurosurgery, Neurology, and Head and Neck patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We nurse highly acute patients, including those with tracheostomy, unstable spinal injury and major head injury. Our patients group is very diverse, with complex cases, as well as routine and emergency neurosurgery/neurology, head and neck and max fax.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experienced staff and newly qualified nurses may apply for this post. If you are keen in developing your nursing career in Neuroscience and Head and Neck to enhance your clinical skills and attain a wide range of experience, we would welcome an application from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are also introducing rotational posts with our stroke and HASU, if interested please raise at your interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: interviews are due to take place on 21-Nov, if you submit an application please ensure you are available on this date.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Theresa Velarde - 12E Ward Manager on 02035945684/42863&lt;/p&gt;
